# Architecture & Module Boundaries

7777 is a compact, single-session SolidJS/Vite UI. Target layout parity with `<repo-root>/packages/app`; see `README.md` → **Code Layout Parity Review** for the current map.

## Layer Responsibilities

| Layer | Role |
|-------|------|
| `src/context/` | Providers, global stores, server/SDK wiring, sync |
| `src/pages/` | Route-level shells and feature composition |
| `src/components/` | Reusable UI; no route or global-store ownership |
| `src/hooks/` | Derived data and side-effect hooks |
| `src/utils/` | Pure helpers (prompt parsing, server URL, UUID) |
| `src/constants/` | Shared constants only |

## Sync & Session Boundaries

- **Server lifecycle**: `server-sync.tsx` owns one active-session SSE lifecycle.
- **Global sync**: `global-sync/bootstrap.ts`, `session-load.ts`, `session-cache.ts`, `event-reducer.ts`, `queue.ts` — keep message cache, event reduction, and refresh timers here, not in `server-session.ts`.
- **UI store**: `server-session.ts` holds global UI state and current-session lookup only.
- **Prompt/composer**: draft state in `context/prompt.tsx`; submit/abort in `components/prompt-input/submit.ts`; composer orchestration under `pages/session/composer/`.
- **Timeline**: projection in `timeline/projection.ts`, rows in `timeline/rows.ts`, types in `timeline/timeline-row.ts`, rendering in `message-timeline.tsx`. No virtualization layer (7777-only omission).

## Parity Rules

When adding or moving a feature that exists in `packages/app`:

1. **Match app filenames and module boundaries** for that feature.
2. **Keep 7777-only code** in place when the compact architecture requires it (e.g. `session-recovery.ts`, `default-model-config.*`, `question.tsx`).
3. **Update `README.md` parity table** in the same change if layout intentionally differs or a new 7777-only module is added.

```text
# ❌ BAD — message cache logic in server-session.ts
# ✅ GOOD — mutate cache via global-sync/session-cache.ts; reducer dispatches from event-reducer.ts

# ❌ BAD — new shared feature as src/lib/my-feature.ts while app uses src/context/my-feature.tsx
# ✅ GOOD — mirror app path: src/context/my-feature.tsx
```

## Intentional 7777 Differences

Do not port app-only multi-session infrastructure: tab router, `session-route.ts`, timeline virtualization (`row-reconciliation`, `virtual-items`, `measure`), command palette (`use-composer-commands`), or `model-variant.ts`.
